address: 180 Gilju-ro, Jung-dong, Wonmi-gu, Bucheon-si, Gyeonggi-do, South Korea

description: Located at the foot of Beiyue Mountain, Sanqing Park was designated as the No. 1 park in Korea in 1940, and its name is derived from the Taoism "Sanqing". The perimeter of the park is surrounded by cherry trees, and around April every year, many people come here to enjoy the cherry blossoms. The park is equipped with badminton courts, tennis courts, children's amusement facilities, various rest spaces, and stores, bringing convenience to citizens who come here to play. The main walking routes in Samcheong Park are: the Bukaksan Seoul Fortress Path that goes up Samcheong-dong, the route that goes along Seongbuk-dong Potion, and the walking path that circulates between Wolong Park. There is Seoul's best observatory, Maam Rock, where you can view the panoramic view of Seoul when you climb up to Maam Rock. In particular, in the "Maam History Visiting Event" (fourth Saturday of every month), accompanied by detailed explanations, not only can people understand the natural environment of Samcheong Park, but also let people understand the city outline of Seoul. A new understanding of history.
